track_notes:
This is the complete trail from the summit of Morro de la Cruz Grande to Morro de la Hierba Huerto following the ridge between these summits. Once you are down from Morro de la Cruz Grande on the forest service road these are all well marked and easy to follow hiking trails.

This is a long hike! If you leave out the first summit and want only to access Hierba Huerto this could be done with a MTB from Degollada de la Cruz Grande.

An alternative, much shorter route leads from the water reservoir of Chira up to Hierba Huerto (no track available).

There are some antenna installations and solar panels on the summit. I had no interference on shortwave, VHF not tried.
track_title: From Morro de la Cruz Grande to Hierba Huerto

track_notes: This trail could be done with a MTB which could be more fun than the long hike!
track_title: back to Degollada de la Cruz Grande

track_notes:
Take this track if you only will activate this summit. It was also advised by PA7ZEE. 
Parking spot near Presa de Chira at 27.904541, -15.640045
(I saw a truck drive the gravel road .. so you could try it, but at a point the road is blocked with a chain anyway).
I took the walk all the way, it took me 1 hour and 45 minutes to reach the summit (including some drink and photo stops). Halfway you can rest at a small cave. Take plenty of water !
On the summit, there is a tree with two big stones, in the shade .. one for you, and one for your rig, hi
track_title: Long walk along a gravel road
Probably the shortest track to EA8/GC-010
